main event: Two civilian security officers observed a bright, oval-shaped white light in the sky near Castle Rock, Colorado on June 6, 1966.
interesting points: The object appeared to be stationary at first, then began moving at a high rate of speed, stopping, oscillating, and then accelerating rapidly in a northeast direction before disappearing.
The object was estimated to be approximately 20-25 feet in diameter and was bright enough to illuminate the surrounding area.
No sound was heard associated with the object.
The security officers reported the incident to their supervisor, who then notified the appropriate authorities.
The sighting lasted for several minutes.
